14/12/2010
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Slovenia supports Macedonia's bids to join the EU and NATO and will lobby to set a date for starting EU accession talks at the upcoming Union summit, Foreign Minister Samuel Zbogar said in a letter to Macedonian counterpart Antonio Milososki on Monday (December 13th).
He praised the progress achieved by Macedonia so far and voiced hope that a solution to the long-standing name dispute with Greece will be found soon.
On Tuesday, the EU General Affairs Council is to discuss the EC progress reports on Western Balkan countries ahead of the European Council session Thursday and Friday.
(MIA, Makfax, Sitel - 12/12/10)
